#!/bin/sh
# Build cclsh and atomically install its matched kernel and image into
# ~/.local/bin. A login shell in /etc/passwd should point at this real
# copy: repository artifacts are gitignored and one git clean -fdx away
# from disappearing.
set -e
cd "$(dirname "$0")/.."
scripts/build
mkdir -p "$HOME/.local/bin"
cp cclsh.image "$HOME/.local/bin/cclsh.image.new"
cp cclsh "$HOME/.local/bin/cclsh.new"
chmod 755 "$HOME/.local/bin/cclsh.new"
mv -f "$HOME/.local/bin/cclsh.image.new" "$HOME/.local/bin/cclsh.image"
mv -f "$HOME/.local/bin/cclsh.new" "$HOME/.local/bin/cclsh"
echo "Installed $HOME/.local/bin/cclsh and its saved image"
